  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Purpose&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Monitor&amp;nbsp;Risk Aging in order to:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        determine whether risks are being addressed&amp;nbsp;in a timely manner, reducing uncertainty in the project&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        understand the capacity of the team to mitigate past risks to help with future planning&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Definition&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Count the number of days it takes for each&amp;nbsp;risk to move from &quot;New&quot; to &quot;Mitigated.&quot; Group by age&amp;nbsp;(e.g. less&#xD;
    than 1 week, 1 to 2 weeks, and more than 2 weeks.).&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    For each age group, calculate&amp;nbsp;a percentage by dividing the number of&amp;nbsp;risks in that&amp;nbsp;age group&amp;nbsp;by the&#xD;
    total number of risks.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Set up an acceptable threshold for the number of days it should take to mitigate risks (this is typically 1 week), and&#xD;
    later use this threshold to assess the performance of the&amp;nbsp;risk management process.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Analysis&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Use a bar chart to monitor&amp;nbsp;Risk Aging. Plot the percentage of&amp;nbsp;risks on the Y axis, and age groups on the X&#xD;
    axis.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Expected Trend&lt;/strong> - Risks are monitored weekly, and all newly identified risks have a mitigation plan in&#xD;
    place within 1 week.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;strong>High percentage of&amp;nbsp;risks&amp;nbsp;taking more than 1 week to mitigate&lt;/strong>&amp;nbsp;(e.g. 1-2 weeks and more&#xD;
    than 2 weeks) - Generally, this signifies that the team does not address&amp;nbsp;risks in a timely manner. Either analysis&#xD;
    is taking too long, or the team is not placing enough priority on reviewing and mitigating risks. Confirm there is&#xD;
    sufficient, consistent process and tooling in place that will alert the team to newly submitted risks and that&#xD;
    necessary information is captured with each report for efficient analysis. Confirm the team works to&amp;nbsp;create a&#xD;
    mitigation plan&amp;nbsp;as quickly as possible for newly identified risks to reduce their probability of occurrence and&#xD;
    potential impact to project health.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Below is an example&amp;nbsp;Risk Aging chart. Percentage of Risks are on the Y axis and age groups (in weeks)&amp;nbsp;are on&#xD;
    the X axis.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img alt=&quot;Risk Aging&quot; src=&quot;resources/risk_aging.gif&quot; width=&quot;600&quot; height=&quot;333&quot; />&amp;nbsp;&lt;br />&#xD;
    &amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Assumptions and prerequisites&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The team has a tool in place to collect risk data, and has identified states for measurement&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Risk&amp;nbsp;status updates are collected with date stamps&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Frequency and reporting&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The team reviews Risk Aging weekly.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Trends are monitored and analyzed to help prioritize activities in the&#xD;
    next iteration planning session. Stakeholders are routinely apprised of current risks and collaborate with the team for&#xD;
    impact assessment and mitigation.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Collection and reporting tools&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Risks can be captured in IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Team Concert&amp;reg;, IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Project Conductor&amp;reg;, IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; ReqPro&amp;reg; using&#xD;
    custom attributes, or in a simple spreadsheet.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Pitfalls, advice, and countermeasures&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        If risk is not managed consistently throughout the lifecycle, the team will likely begin to act in a reactive,&#xD;
        crisis mode as risks emerge. A consistent, repeatable risk mitigation process enables better project predictability&#xD;
        and higher levels of trust by project stakeholders.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The need to identify and monitor risk increases with the complexity of the system.The effort to reduce uncertainty&#xD;
        has an associated cost. The team must balance the cost of this effort against the potential impact of not&#xD;
        addressing the risk. Not all candidate risks are actively managed. Mitigation effort and degree of monitoring&#xD;
        depend on the likelihood of impact and the risk tolerance for the project.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br /></mainDescription>
